losophy is not a separate area of philosophy that can safely be ignored by philosophers not "in" it. Rather, it relates to at least most of the major areas of philosophy, and its gains will stand to benefit all philosophers, no matter what their field.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aCritique féministe. 0aFeminist criticism. 0aFeminist theory. 0aThéorie féministe. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Ethics & Moral Philosophy.2bisacsh1 aAntony, Louise M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBordo, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCode, Lorraine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrankenberry, Nancy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeld, Virginia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKorsmeyer, Carolyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKourany, Janet A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKourany, Janet A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMoller Okin, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNye, Andrea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aO’Neill, Eileen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999z978311044249640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978140082232440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781400822324423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781400822324.jpg  a978-3-11-044249-6  Princeton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999c1927d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_